# Product Requirements Document (PRD)

## DeepSOW  
**Version:** 1.0  
**Date:** 2026-03-07  
**Author:** Product Team  

---

## 1. Executive Summary

DeepSOW is a next-generation Statement of Work (SOW) analyzer that leverages AI to automatically extract, structure, and visualize key commitments from SOW documents. It provides a centralized dashboard for tracking deliverables, spend, compliance, and value realization across the entire contract lifecycle. Built for procurement, professional services, legal, and finance teams, DeepSOW eliminates manual data entry, reduces errors, and ensures that what was promised is actually delivered.

---

## 2. Problem Statement

Organizations managing multiple SOWs face a critical lack of visibility:

- **Fragmented processes:** SOWs are scattered across Word documents, PDFs, and emails.
- **Manual extraction:** Teams spend hours manually reading contracts and copying data into spreadsheets.
- **No tracking of commitments:** Once a project starts, there is no easy way to verify that deliverables align with the original SOW.
- **Compliance risks:** Unclear terms lead to disputes and missed obligations.
- **Revenue leakage:** Undelivered or under-delivered services go unnoticed until renewal.

> *“Most services teams can tell you what they shipped, but not whether it matches what was sold.”* — Industry Analyst

DeepSOW solves this by creating a single source of truth for every SOW, enabling real‑time insight and proactive management.

---

## 3. Target Audience & User Personas

| Persona | Role | Key Need |
|--------|------|----------|
| **Procurement Manager** | Oversees services procurement | Visibility into all active SOWs, spend tracking, compliance. |
| **Professional Services Lead** | Manages delivery teams | Ensure project deliverables match SOW commitments. |
| **Legal Counsel** | Reviews contracts | Quick access to clauses, version history, audit trail. |
| **Finance Analyst** | Tracks budget vs. actual | Accurate spend data, forecasting, invoice validation. |
| **Sales / Account Executive** | Renews contracts | Proof of delivered value to present at renewal. |

---

## 4. Product Goals & Objectives

1. **Automate SOW data extraction** – Reduce manual effort by 90% using AI.
2. **Provide real‑time dashboard** – Give stakeholders a unified view of all SOW commitments, status, and spend.
3. **Enable commitment tracking** – Link deliverables to evidence and measure delivery against promise.
4. **Improve compliance** – Flag deviations and ensure audit‑ready documentation.
5. **Drive renewals** – Generate value‑realization reports for clients.

---

## 5. Feature Requirements

### **5.1 Core Features (Must Have)**

| ID | Feature | Description | User Benefit |
|----|---------|-------------|--------------|
| F1 | **AI‑Powered SOW Parsing** | Upload SOW (PDF, DOCX) → OpenAI extracts key fields: parties, deliverables, milestones, pricing, dates, clauses. | No manual data entry. |
| F2 | **Unified Dashboard** | Central view of all SOWs with filters by status, client, date. Cards show summary metrics (total value, active SOWs, upcoming milestones). | Instant overview. |
| F3 | **Commitment Extraction** | Identify measurable commitments (e.g., “deliver 5 training sessions”, “develop mobile app”). Normalize into structured items. | Track exactly what was promised. |
| F4 | **Milestone Tracking** | Display each milestone with due date, status (Not Started / In Progress / Completed / At Risk), and linked evidence. | Never miss a deadline. |
| F5 | **Spend vs. Budget** | Compare actual spend (from integrated ERP or manual entry) against SOW budget. | Prevent cost overruns. |
| F6 | **Evidence Attachment** | Attach files, emails, or notes to specific commitments (e.g., client sign‑off, meeting minutes). | Build audit trail. |
| F7 | **User & Role Management** | Admin can invite team members, assign roles (viewer, editor, admin), and set permissions. | Secure collaboration. |

### **5.2 Advanced Features (Should Have)**

| ID | Feature | Description | User Benefit |
|----|---------|-------------|--------------|
| F8 | **Smart Search & Filter** | Search across all SOWs by keyword, client, date range, or custom fields. | Find any SOW in seconds. |
| F9 | **Clause Library** | Automatically tag common clauses (IP, termination, confidentiality). Users can browse/search clause occurrences. | Legal review speed. |
| F10 | **Compliance Alerts** | Notify when a deliverable is overdue, spend exceeds threshold, or a key clause is triggered. | Proactive risk management. |
| F11 | **Value Realization Report** | Generate a PDF report showing “Promised vs. Delivered” for a specific SOW, including evidence links. | Client renewals. |
| F12 | **Integration Hub** | Connect with Salesforce (pull opportunity data), Jira (link deliverables), QuickBooks/Xero (pull spend). | Eliminate silos. |
| F13 | **Template Standardization** | Provide a library of SOW templates; guide users through scoping questions to create new SOWs with consistent language. | Better initial SOWs. |

### **5.3 Future Enhancements (Could Have)**

| ID | Feature | Description |
|----|---------|-------------|
| F14 | **Version Comparison** | Compare two versions of an SOW and highlight changes. |
| F15 | **AI‑Powered Risk Scoring** | Automatically assess SOW risk based on language (e.g., vague deliverables, missing dates). |
| F16 | **Multi‑language Support** | Parse SOWs in multiple languages using OpenAI. |
| F17 | **Mobile App** | Lightweight mobile dashboard for executives. |

---

## 6. Technical Architecture (High‑Level)

DeepSOW will be built using modern, scalable technologies:

- **Frontend:** Next.js (React framework) with **shadcn/ui** for beautiful, accessible components. Hosted on Vercel or AWS Amplify.
- **Backend API:** FastAPI (Python) – provides REST endpoints for document upload, AI processing, and data retrieval. Deployed on AWS Lambda (serverless) or EC2.
- **Database:** AWS DynamoDB – NoSQL, highly scalable, ideal for document‑oriented data. Tables for SOWs, commitments, users, etc.
- **AI Layer:** OpenAI API (GPT‑4) – for parsing and extracting structured data from SOW texts. Prompt engineering will ensure high accuracy.
- **File Storage:** AWS S3 – store original SOW files and evidence attachments.
- **Authentication:** NextAuth.js or AWS Cognito – secure user login.
- **Integrations:** Custom connectors via FastAPI; webhooks for real‑time sync.

**Data Flow:**
1. User uploads SOW via Next.js frontend → file stored in S3.
2. Backend FastAPI triggers OpenAI to extract data → structured JSON stored in DynamoDB.
3. Dashboard queries DynamoDB via API and displays insights.
4. Evidence attachments and updates follow similar flow.

